ce:section.ce:para:
The UV/Vis absorption spectra of the Pcs and conjugates are shown in Fig. 1
                        . Phthalocyanines have characteristic Q and B bands in absorption spectra, these were observed for both compounds (Table 1
                        ) [38,39]. Compound 1 had a strong absorption Q band at 676 nm while the B band was observed at 332 nm and compound 2 had the Q and B bands at 660 nm (Table 1) and 332 nm respectively. There is a blue shift for compound 2 compared to 1 due to the reduction in the number of dimethylamino groups. Nitrogen-containing groups are known to result in red shifting in MPc complexes [41]. The mass spectroscopic experiments were carried out using α-cyano-4-hydroxycinnamic acid matrix. The calculated mass for compound 1 was 1148.59 amu and 1139.48 amu for compound 2, these masses were in agreement with that determined experimentally.
